      "date": "2013-05-29 18:18:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi JC, maybe I missed something here. If restore revokes layout lock, why the lvb of layout lock can't be refreshed?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "541a08adc17c2b9c0b3b81b341124cd2320ad54c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-29 20:08:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIn restore case the layout move from a released one to a valid one. So the lvb_data is already allocated. In ll_layout_fetch() the refresh was not done if LDLM_FL_LVB_READY was set or if the  lvb_data was allocated. The patch just do the refresh in these cases.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
